import java.util.*;

public class Q1 {
    static class TokenBucketLimiter {
        private final double capacity, refillRatePerMs;
        private final Map<String, double[]> state = new HashMap<>();

        TokenBucketLimiter(double capacity, double refillPerSec) {
            this.capacity = capacity;
            this.refillRatePerMs = refillPerSec / 1000.0;
        }

        public synchronized boolean allow(String userId) {
            long now = System.currentTimeMillis();
            double[] s = state.computeIfAbsent(userId, k -> new double[]{capacity, now});
            double elapsed = now - s[1];
            s[0] = Math.min(capacity, s[0] + elapsed * refillRatePerMs);
            s[1] = now;
            if (s[0] >= 1) { s[0]--; return true; }
            return false;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        TokenBucketLimiter rl = new TokenBucketLimiter(3, 1);
        System.out.println(rl.allow("alice")); // true
        System.out.println(rl.allow("alice")); // true
        System.out.println(rl.allow("alice")); // true
        System.out.println(rl.allow("alice")); // false
        Thread.sleep(2000);
        System.out.println(rl.allow("alice")); // true
    }
}

problems.description:
Implement refresh token rotation for secure session management.

**Flow:**
```
1. Login → access_token (15min) + refresh_token (7d, stored in DB)
2. Access token expires
3. POST /auth/refresh with refresh_token
4. Server: validate token, issue NEW access + NEW refresh, invalidate old refresh
5. Repeat
```

```java
@PostMapping("/auth/refresh")
public TokenResponse refresh(@RequestBody RefreshRequest req) {
    RefreshToken rt = refreshTokenRepo.findByToken(req.getToken())
        .orElseThrow(() -> new InvalidTokenException());
    if (rt.getExpiresAt().isBefore(Instant.now()))
        throw new TokenExpiredException();
    refreshTokenRepo.delete(rt); // invalidate old token (rotation)
    String newRefresh = UUID.randomUUID().toString();
    refreshTokenRepo.save(new RefreshToken(rt.getUser(), newRefresh, Instant.now().plusSeconds(604800)));
    return new TokenResponse(jwtService.generate(rt.getUser()), newRefresh);
}
```

**Key insight:** Token rotation = if refresh token is stolen and used, the legitimate user's next refresh fails → detects theft. Short-lived access tokens limit breach window.

